messages.message: Hey all, in aihub-sandbox and aihub-uat, I get a blank page when I load the landing page in Firefox. There are also some JS type errors (see below)
On the other hand, `/workspaces` loads fine; one of the two console errors is not there (still see the one about script-src)
Chrome loads OK, but has a different set of console errors
EDIT: Actually, Chrome does NOT load OK when I sign in:
I'm not able to reproduce this, so my guess is it's something in your local storage that isn't be stored/retrieved properly
cc @Weiming Wu, I'll also investigate
Is there any chance you have a data source mounted that does not have a label in `DEFAULT_MOUNT_NAME` const in MountTypes.ts
And does the page also break if you go directly to Search?
Actually, if you can send me the login info you're using this might be easier to debug
Yeah sure -- 1 sec!
Ah, it's my SSO account. Let me create another account w/ a password and reproduce it.
Reproduced it. Will send you login into now

So I thinkkkk this is because "confluence" is lowercased in the client_type of one of your org drives. We're looking for "confluence" exactly in a dict and not finding it because we expect "Confluence"
The only place we're using these constants in this way is in the search bar, so it makes sense that it would just break on the homepage
Was that one added manually? I don't see anywhere in the codebase we're using "confluence" lowercased as a constant

It's probably one that was manually added way back (UAT/sandbox are pretty crufty data-wise). I can find the mount point(s) and then clean it up. Hopefully doesn't recur!

Long-term, I have a proposal to fix this by using a proper database column for storing the client type/connector type w/ a check constraint, so that we don't have these kinds of runtime errors.
`01946070-b78d-77a8-9048-0a1769036ddf`  I think is the problem:
Yep, that fixed it. Thanks @Jessica!
Yup that's the one!
In sandbox, there are 3-4 of these; I'll remove them all
